giveness%20and%20tax%20cuts%2C%20economist%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221918%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Capitol%20building%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65dce2326080194819fa3dca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22959%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Capitol%20building%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20US%20wants%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20enact%20fiscal%20measures%20like%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20and%20tax%20cuts%2C%20Piper%20Sandler's%20chief%20global%20economist%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDrivers%20of%20US%20growth%20seen%20during%201995's%20soft%20landing%20aren't%20currently%20present%2C%20so%20government%20spending%20may%20be%20necessary%20to%20buoy%20GDP%2C%20according%20to%20Nancy%20Lazar.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThere%20could%20easily%20be%20an%20additional%201.5%25%20boost%20to%20GDP%20from%20fiscal%20stimulus%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20US%20economy%20wants%20to%20stick%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20the%20government%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20loosen%20the%20purse%20strings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20says%20Piper%20Sandler's%20chief%20global%20economist%20Nancy%20Lazar.%20She%20argues%20that%20without%20traditional%20drivers%20of%20growth%20fueling%20the%20economy%2C%20avoiding%20a%20recession%20will%20require%20some%20fiscal%20largesse%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loans-where-does-biden-debt-cancellation-stand-negotiations-relief-2024-2%5C%22%3Estudent-loan-forgiveness%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20tax%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20order%20to%20have%20a%20soft%20landing%20in%202024%2C%20additional%20fiscal%20stimulus%20would%20be%20needed%20(such%20stimulus%20definitely%20kept%20the%20economy%20stronger%2C%20longer%20in%202023)%2C%26quot%3B%20Lazar%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20times%20in%20history%20that%20the%20US%20has%20been%20able%20to%20nail%20a%20soft%20landing%3A%201967%2C%201985%2C%20and%201995.%20But%20Lazar%20notes%20that%20there%20are%20certain%20factors%20that%20helped%20the%20economy%20land%20softly%20during%20those%20eras%20then%20that%20are%20absent%20today%2C%20like%20easy%20commercial-bank-lending%20standards%20(present%20all%20three%20times)%2C%20growing%20real%20revenues%20for%20corporations%20(present%20in%201995)%2C%20and%20an%20uninverted%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-inverted-yield-curve-inventor-financial-markets-investors-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyield%20curve%3C%2Fa%3E%20(present%20in%201995).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20those%20typical%20boosters%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20won't%20prop%20up%20growth%20in%202024%2C%20it'll%20have%20to%20come%20from%20somewhere%20else.%20That's%20where%20the%20government%20comes%20in%2C%20according%20to%20Lazar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20says%20possibile%20measures%20include%20student-loan%20forgiveness%2C%20doling%20out%20grants%20under%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%2C%20and%20proposals%20like%20the%20Wyden-Smith%20tax%20cut%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20sitting%20in%20the%20Senate.%20There%20are%20also%20other%20factors%20like%20employment%20retention%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPutting%20all%20the%20above%20together%2C%20there%20could%20easily%20be%20an%20additional%201.5%25%20boost%20to%20GDP%20from%20fiscal%20stimulus%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20raise%20Piper%20Sandler's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-gdp-fourth-quarter-of-2023-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DReal%2520GDP%2520grew%2520at%2520an%2Cpoint%2520suggests%2520still%2520strong%2520growth.%5C%22%3Ereal%20GDP%20forecast%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%200.5%25%20expansion%20this%20year%2C%20instead%20a%201%25%20contraction.%20For%20context%2C%20they're%20on%20the%20more%20bearish%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fpublication%2F59946%23_idTextAnchor094%5C%22%3ECongressional%20Budget%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20currently%20expects%20more%20robust%20growth%20of%201.5%25%20in%202024.%20Meanwhile%2C%20economists%20surveyed%20by%20Bloomberg%20see%202%25%20expansion%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20drawback%20to%20this%20approach%20is%20that%20it%20would%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20in%20the%20face%20of%20such%20a%20strong%20economic%20backdrop.%20In%20the%20previous%20instance%20of%201967%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Bill%20Martin%20boosted%20GDP%2C%20pushed%20unemployment%20lower%2C%20and%20sent%20stocks%20soaring%20%E2%80%94%20hardly%20conditions%20conducive%20for%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELazar%20cites%201967%20as%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20in%20the%20event%20the%20Fed%20enacts%20fiscal%20measures%20to%20further%20stimulate%20the%20economy.%20After%20the%20late-1960s%20boom%20time%2C%20the%20US%20eventually%20battled%20runaway%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEasing%20amid%20material%20fiscal%20stimulus%20risks%20repeating%20the%20Martin%20Fed's%20mistake...which%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%201970s'%20disastrous%20inflation%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-soft-landing-student-loan-forgiveness-tax-cuts-policy-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708981641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65dce214ce7f1785b2e3f6f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-soft-landing-student-loan-forgiveness-tax-cuts-policy-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Drivers%20of%20US%20growth%20present%20