s-interest-rates-stay-high-report-124022601298_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fwhirlpool-accelerates-debt-reduction-as-interest-rates-stay-high-report-124022601298_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BNot%20Freedom%20Of%20Speech%26quot%3B%3A%20Minister%20On%20Space%20To%20Khalistani%20Elements%20Abroad%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20called%20out%20the%20space%20given%20to%20extremist%20Khalistani%20elements%20in%20foreign%20countries%20and%20said%20this%20is%20not%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20but%20a%20misuse%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20is%20not%20good%20for%20any%20country%20to%20send%20that%20kind%20of%20message%20for%20their%20own%20reputation%20and%20expressed%20hope%20that%20action%20will%20be%20taken%20against%20those%20who%20attacked%20Indian%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Minister%20was%20speaking%20at%20the%20event%20'The%20Rise%20of%20the%20Global%20South'%20at%20TV9%20Bharatvarsh%20Conclave%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20situation%20in%20Canada%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20suspend%20the%20issue%20of%20visas%20in%20Canada%20because%20our%20diplomats%20were%20not%20safe%20going%20to%20work%2C%20they%20were%20repeatedly%20threatened%2C%20intimidated%2C%20and%20got%20very%20little%20comfort%20from%20the%20Canadian%20system%20at%20that%20time...which%20has%20improved%20since%20then.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20reached%20a%20stage%2C%20where%2C%20as%20a%20minister%2C%20I%20could%20not%20risk%20exposing%20my%20diplomats%20to%20the%20kind%20of%20violence%20prevalent%20there.%20That%20part%20of%20it%20has%20been%20rectified%2C%20so%20today%20our%20visa%20operations%20are%20pretty%20much%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Minister%20further%20called%20out%20the%20argument%20of%20'freedom%20of%20expression'%20stating%20that%20throwing%20smoke%20bombs%20at%20missions%20and%20advocating%20violence%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bmisuse%26quot%3B%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegarding%20the%20space%20that%20is%20being%20given%20to%20extremists%2C%20they%20keep%20telling%20us%2C%20'There%20is%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20democracy'.%20Freedom%20of%20speech%20can't%20extend%20to%20intimidating%20diplomats%2C%20throwing%20smoke%20bombs%20in%20embassies%20and%20consulates%2C%20advocating%20violence%20and%20separatism%20against%20a%20friendly%20state.%20To%20me%2C%20this%20is%20not%20freedom%20of%20speech.%20This%20is%20a%20misuse%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20vandalism%20incident%20on%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20mission%20didn't%20get%20the%20protection%20New%20Delhi%20had%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20point%20of%20someone%20climbing%20on%20to%20our%20HC%20and%20bringing%20down%20our%20Indian%20flag.%20I%20asked%20my%20colleagues%20'Let's%20put%20us%20in%20each%20other's%20shoes'.%20How%20would%20you%20react%20if%20a%20mob%20attacked%20your%20premises%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%3F%20You%20will%20not%20say%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%2C%20you%20will%20be%20jumping%20up%20and%20down.%20But%2C%20things%20have%20improved%20in%20the%20UK%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20stern%20message%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20if%20a%20country%20is%20not%20taking%20action%20against%20someone%20attacking%20foreign%20missions%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20a%20message%20in%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20had%20a%20much%20firmer%20response%20in%20Australia%20and%20the%20US.%20We%20had%20an%20arson%20attack%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20that%20is%20under%20investigation.%20If%20the%20receiving%20state%20does%20not%20take%20action%20against%20someone%20who%20attacks%20an%20embassy%20or%20a%20consulate%2C%20there's%20a%20message%20in%20it.%20Now%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20good%20for%20any%20country%20to%20send%20that%20kind%20of%20message%20for%20their%20own%20reputation.%20That's%20why%20we%20want%20action%20to%20be%20taken%20against%20those%20who%20attacked%20our%20missions%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20Khalistani%20extremism%20in%20several%20countries%20like%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20killing%20of%20the%20designated%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20last%20June%2C%20the%20Khalistani%20extremists%20targeted%20Indian%20diplomats%20in%20several%20countries%20and%20issued%20threats%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEspecially%20in%20Canada%2C%20multiple%20incidents%20of%20Khalistan%20extremism%20were%20reported%20lately.%20In%20June%20this%20year%2C%20a%20tableau%20parade%20was%20organised%20in%20Canada%20celebrating%20the%20assassination%20of%20former%20PM%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20which%20drew%20severe%20criticism%20from%20New%20Delhi.%20Multiple%20temples%20were%20also%20vandalised%20in%20Canada%20by%20pro-Khalistani%20protestors%2C%20with%20anti-India%20graffiti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20strained%20ties%2C%20India%20stopped%20issuing%20visas%20to%20Canada%20amid%20concerns%20over%20the%20safety%20of%20Indian%20envoys%20there.%20Later%2C%20the%20e-visa%20service%20was%20resumed%2C%20and%20physical%20visa%20was%20also%20started%20in%20multiple%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%20a%20group%20of%20extremist%20elements%20attacked%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20London%20last%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20Consulate%20General%20of%20India%20in%20San%20Francisco%20was%20attacked%20on%20March%2019%20by%20a%20group%20of%20assailants.%20Subsequently%2C%20on%20July%202%2C%20at%20midnight%2C%20a%20few%20people%20a