C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20court%20in%20Bangladesh%20has%20sentenced%20Yunus%20to%20six%20months%20in%20jail%20for%20violating%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20labour%20laws.%20The%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-67858016%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20has%20failed%20%E2%80%98to%20create%20a%20welfare%20fund%20for%20workers%20of%20Grameen%20Telecom%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20venture%20to%20which%20he%20was%20affiliated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrowing%20light%20on%20whether%20the%20verdict%20was%20justified%2C%20Professor%20Rehman%20Sobhan%2C%20a%20close%20friend%20of%20Indian%20Nobel%20Laureate%20Amartya%20Sen%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Fopinion%2Fviews%2Fnews%2Fwhom-the-bell-tolls-3523086%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9COver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20legal%20system%20has%20become%20an%20element%20in%20the%20wider%20assault%20on%20our%20institutions%20of%20democracy%20and%20governance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbangladesh-court-convicts-nobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-in-labour-law-case%5C%22%3EBangladesh%20Court%20Convicts%20Nobel%20Laureate%20Muhammad%20Yunus%20in%20Labour%20Law%20Case%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20reactions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2015%2C%20the%20UN%20Secretary%20General%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20Stephane%20Dujarric%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justnewsbd.com%2Fen%2Funited-nations%2Fnews%2F21607%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20harsh%20measures%20against%20Yunus%20and%20whether%20the%20UN%20Secretary%20General%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20very%20much%20aware.%20I%E2%80%99d%20have%20to%20reiterate%20that%20Dr%20Yunus%20has%20been%20a%20very%20much%20valued%20partner%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20through%20the%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%E2%80%99s%20been%20an%20advocate%20for%20us%20both%20in%20official%20and%20unofficial%20capacity%20and%20supporting%20a%20number%20of%20the%20UN%20initiatives.%20We%20are%20very%20concerned%20about%20the%20reports%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20coming%20out%20of%20Bangladesh%20on%20issues%20related%20to%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dujarric%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20expressed%20similar%20concerns%20while%20sounding%20a%20note%20of%20caution%20about%20wider%20abuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrincipal%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20state%20department%20Mathew%20Miller%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fbriefings%2Fdepartment-press-briefing-february-13-2024%2F%23BANGLADESH%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20share%20the%20concerns%20voiced%20by%20other%20international%20observers%20that%20these%20cases%20may%20represent%20a%20misuse%20of%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20labour%20laws%20to%20harass%20and%20intimidate%20Dr.%20Yunus%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20worry%20the%20perceived%20misuse%20of%20labour%20and%20anti-corruption%20laws%20could%20raise%20questions%20about%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20dissuade%20future%20foreign%20direct%20investment%2C%20and%20we%20encourage%20the%20Bangladeshi%20Government%20to%20ensure%20a%20fair%20and%20transparent%20legal%20process%20for%20Dr.%20Yunus%20as%20the%20appeals%20process%20continues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20series%20of%20open%20letters%2C%20expressing%20international%20concern%20and%20appeals%2C%20global%20leaders%20consistently%20addressed%20the%20unjust%20targeting%20of%20Yunus.%20For%20instance%2C%20242%20global%20leaders%2C%20including%20125%20Nobel%20Laureates%2C%20expressed%20deep%20concern%20in%20a%20letter%20written%20in%20late%20January%20over%20his%20continuous%20judicial%20harassment%20and%20potential%20jailing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20bipartisan%20group%20of%2012%20US%20senators%20wrote%20to%20Hasina%20asking%20her%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20persistent%20harassment.%20The%20senators%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.durbin.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fsenate_letter_to_pm_hasina_re_profyunus.pdf%5C%22%3Eexpressed%3C%2Fa%3E%20concern%20over%20more%20than%20150%20unsubstantiated%20cases%20brought%20against%20Yunus%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20highlighting%20irregularities%20in%20the%20legal%20proceedings%20and%20the%20use%20of%20criminal%20charges%2C%20which%20they%20argue%20are%20politically%20motivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Yunus%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20Hasina%20has%20been%20coming%20heavy-handedly%20after%20Yunus.%20She%20frequently%20frames%20him%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Fjan%2F01%2Fnobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-convicted-bangladesh%5C%22%3Ebloodsucker%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98usurer%E2%80%99%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20critics%20say%20Hasina%20expresses%20her%20wrath%20regarding%20Yunus%20because%20the%20world%20recognises%20him%20way%20more%20than%20her%20or%20her%20father%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman.%20Some%20even%20wonder%20if%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20is%20the%20root%20cause%20for%20her%20persecution%20of%20Yunus%2C%20as%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20receive%20the%20honour%20while%20her%20party%20loyalists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhakatribune.com%2Fbangladesh%2F306478%2Fminister-pm-hasina-should-have-been-awarded-nobel%5C%22%3Eargue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20was%20more%20worthy%20than%20Yunus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20global%20recognition%20is%20a%20concern%20for%20Hasina%2C%20she%20should%20be%20proud%20that%20the%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%20crowned%20her%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsf.org%2Fen%2Fprotagonist-sheikh-hasina%5C%22%3EPredator%20of%20Press%20Freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%208%2C%20right%20after%20her%20victory%20in%20the%20sham%20elections%2C%20an%20Indian%20journalist%20asked%20the%20Awami%20League%20leader%20if%20she%20would%20be%20pardoning%20Yunus%20as%20a%20good%20faith%20gesture%20after%20winning%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Felection-2024%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fyunus-should-apologise-his-workers-pm-3514466%5C%22%3Ereplied%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20the%20labour%20court.%20The%20workers%20of%20his%20own%20organisation%20are%20deprived.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20nothing%20to%20do%20here.%20This%20question%20of%20pardoning%20him%20should%20not%20come%20to%20me.%20Rather%2C%20he%20should%20seek%20an%20apology%20from%20his%20workers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20many%20observers%2C%20Yunus%20has%20not%20been%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20authoritarian%20regime%2C%20her%20gruesome%20human%20rights%20records%20or%20muzzling%20political%20dissents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20he%20faced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Flive%2FZrVwJ2iAgNs%3Fsi%3DP-__xsjw_MWio37h%5C%22%3Equestion%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20%3Cem%3EDW%20Bangla%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20why%20he%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20outspoken%20about%20the%20absence%20of%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh.%20In%20his%20defence%2C%20Yunus%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%98unwarranted%20consequences%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20the%20controversial%20jail%20term%20against%20him%2C%20Yunus%20made%20an%20attempt%20to%20speak%20for%20human%20rights%20and%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Yunus%E2%80%99%20daughter%20Monica%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2Fvideos%2Ftv%2F2024%2F01%2F29%2Famanpour-muhammad-yunus-daughter-monica-bangladesh.cnn%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Christiane%20Amanpour%20that%20her%20father%20once%20worked%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Hasina.%20Would%20there%20be%2