overnment%20has%20blocked%20access%20to%20social%20media%20platform%20X%20(previously%20known%20as%20Twitter)%20though%20it%20occasionally%20remains%20accessible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20crackdown%20began%20on%20February%208%2C%202024%2C%20the%20day%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20election%2C%20when%20mobile%20services%20and%20social%20media%20were%20initially%20suspended.%20Surprisingly%2C%20these%20suspensions%20have%20persisted%20continuously%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20censorship%20challenges%2C%20Pakistan%20struggles%20to%20preserve%20free%20speech%2C%20which%20has%20become%20increasingly%20difficult%20as%20dozens%20of%20journalists%20and%20media%20professionals%20have%20received%20notices%20from%20the%20Federal%20Investigation%20Agency%20(FIA)%20for%20participating%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pakistanpressfoundation.org%2Fheadline-ppf-alarmed-by-fia-notices-to-media-professionals-for-campaign-against-supreme-court-judges-urge-the-government-to-ensure-free-expression-rather-than-clamp-down-on-it%2F%5C%22%3Eexplicit%20and%20malicious%20campaign%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20judges%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Pakistan.%20Recently%2C%20two%20journalists%20were%20arrested%2C%20one%20of%20them%20was%20released%20after%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20journalists%20started%20criticising%20the%20unfair%20treatment%20towards%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaaf%20(PTI)%20leaders%2C%20and%20restrictions%20were%20imposed%20on%20discussions%20of%20the%20allegations%20of%20rigged%20election%20and%20media%20and%20journalists%2C%20in%20general%2C%20tensions%20have%20escalated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamid%20Mir%2C%20a%20prominent%20senior%20journalist%2C%20who%20faces%20restrictions%20and%20in%202014%20was%20shot%20and%20wounded%20for%20his%20free%20speech%2C%20continues%20to%20highlight%20issues%20despite%20these%20challenges.%20Mir%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20restrictions%20on%20Pakistani%20TV%20media%2C%20where%20journalists%20are%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20allowed%20to%20pronounce%20the%20name%20of%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnly%20a%20small%20number%20of%20journalists%2C%20including%20myself%20can%20mention%20Imran%20Khan%20by%20name%20on%20the%20TV%20show%3B%20others%20refer%20to%20him%20as%20chairman%20of%20PTI%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mir%20said.%20This%20stricter%20censorship%20on%20media%20even%20extends%20to%20naming%20political%20party%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPakistan%20interim%20government%20Prime%20Minister%20Anwaarul%20Haq%20Kakar%20claims%20that%20%E2%80%98Pakistani%20media%20is%20freer%20than%20the%20West.%E2%80%99%20The%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20social%20media%20is%20restricted%20and%20journalists%20cannot%20mention%20Imran%20Khan%20by%20his%20name%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%20imposition%20of%20the%20social%20media%20restrictions%20and%20internet%20shutdowns%2C%20US%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%20Matthew%20Miller%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20concerned%20by%20any%20reports%20of%20restrictions%20on%20the%20exercise%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20association%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20including%20the%20partial%20or%20complete%20government-imposed%20internet%20shutdown%2C%20which%20includes%2C%20of%20course%2C%20on%20social%20media%20platforms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnannounced%20censorship%20tightens%20grip%20in%20Pakistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfrasiab%20Khattak%2C%20senior%20politician%20and%20analyst%2C%20warns%20of%20growing%20authoritarianism%2C%20exemplified%20by%20escalating%20media%20censorship%20under%20the%20caretaker%20government.%20This%20crackdown%20includes%20restrictions%20on%20mainstream%20and%20social%20media%2C%20notably%20the%20unprecedented%20blocking%20of%20platform%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20suppression%20of%20free%20speech%20is%20alarming%20as%20platform%20X%20is%20vital%20for%20journalists%2C%20activists%20and%20citizens%20to%20express%20themselves%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-the-only-certainty-after-a-rigged-election-is-chaos%5C%22%3EPakistan%3A%20The%20Only%20Certainty%20After%20a%20Rigged%20Election%20Is%20Chaos%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInformation%20minister%20of%20caretaker%20government%2C%20Murtaza%20Solangi%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Flive%2Felections-2024%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDawn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnguramani%2Fstatus%2F1761033494052983108%3Ft%3D4YKc1YvHkHWRMpa8nfMlJA%26s%3D08%5C%22%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CInternet%20services%20and%20X%20are%20two%20separate%20things.%20As%20a%20minister%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20suspend%20X.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20literature%20event%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20Mir%20mentioned%2C%20he%20highlighted%20the%20presence%20of%20unannounced%20censorship%20in%20Pakistan%20in%20Solangi%E2%80%99s%20presence.%20The%20minister%20remained%20silent%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20comment%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20Mir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20minister%E2%80%99s%20denial%20contradicts%20the%20suspension%20of%20mobile%20services%20and%20internet.%20This%20action%20also%20violated%20a%20decision%20by%20the%20Sindh%20High%20Court%2C%20which%20ordered%20not%20to%20suspend%20internet%20and%20mobile%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Solangi%E2%80%99s%20denial%2C%20Mir%E2%80%99s%20response%20underlines%20that%20it%20is%20the%20establishment%20that%20actually%20runs%20the%20system%2C%20not%20Solangi.%20Mir%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPakistanis%20know%20what%20fact%20is.%20Those%20who%20brought%20him%2C%20including%20all%20those%20who%20control%20the%20interim%20government%2C%20he%20is%20their%20spokesperson%20and%20they%20both%20speak%20lie.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsad%20Ali%20Toor%2C%20independent%20journalist%2C%20who%20was%20beaten%20in%202021%20for%20his%20work%2C%20was%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1816559%2Fasad-ali-toor-interrogated-for-hours-by-fia-in-connection-with-alleged-campaign-against-superior-judiciary%5C%22%3Einterrogated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Federal%20Investigation%20Agency%20(FIA)%20for%20hours%20after%20he%20spoke%20out%20vocally%20about%20the%20rigged%20elections.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20(Solangi)%20does%20not%20speak%20the%20truth%2C%E2%80%9D%20Toor%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Pakistan%20interim%20government%20even%20%E2%80%9Crefused%20to%20accept%20that%20Baloch%20women%20were%20tortured%20in%20Islamabad.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20caretaker%20government%20attempted%20to%20suppress%20criticism%20and%20manipulate%20the%20elections%20results%20in%20their%20favour%20but%20they%20failed%20to%20silence%20critics%20and%20achieve%20their%20desired%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20coming%20days%2C%20strict%20restrictions%20and%20laws%20to%20be%20imposed%20on%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhattak%20said%20that%20unfortunately%2C%20these%20political%20parties%20which%20will%20be%20forming%20the%20government%20in%20coming%20days%2C%20like%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League%20(Nawaz)%20%5BPMLN%5D%2C%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20%5BPPP%5D%2C%20and%20Muttahida%20Qaumi%20Movement%20(Pakistan)%20%5BMQM-P%5D%20are%20yet%20to%20criticise%20these%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPreviously%2C%20we%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20parties%20like%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League%20(Q)%20%5BPML-Q%5D%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98King%E2%80%99s%20party%E2%80%99.%20Now%2C%20we%20have%20witnessed%20most%20political%20parties%20become%20King%E2%80%99s%20party%2C%20and%20regrettably%2C%20they%20have%20accepted%20such%20restrictions%20on%20free%20speech%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khattak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20accepting%20the%20results%20of%20the%20rigged%20elections%2C%20which%20has%20further%20distorted%20the%20political%20culture.%20They%20seem%20to%20prioritise%20power%20over%20the%20preservation%20of%20free%20speech.%20The%20military%20establishment%20holds%20significant%20power%20and%20allows%20governance%20only%20on%20their%20terms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhattak%20suggested%20that%20this%20restriction%20trend%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20ending%20anytime%20soon%20and%20Pakistan%20needs%20a%20new%20struggle%20for%20democracy%20and%20free%20speech.%20Similarly%2C%20Toor%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20cases%20of%20curbing%20free%20speech%20and%20media%20will%20increase%20and%20he%20feared%20that%20the%20new%20government%20may%20impose%20stricter%20restrictions%20and%20laws%20on%20social%20media%20and%20traditional%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttacking%20the%20governments%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20Mir%20said%20that%20in%20the%20recent%20times%2C%20every%20government%20%E2%80%93%20including%20those%20led%20by%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20Shahbaz%20Sharif%20or%20caretaker%20regime%20%E2%80%93%20has%20curbed%20free%20speech%20more%20severely%20than%20the%20previous%20one.%20%E2%80%9CConsequently%2C%20Pakistani%20media%20will%20likely%20face%20even%20harder%20times%20regarding%20free%20speech%20in%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Democracy%20Index%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsouthasiapress.org%2F2024%2F02%2F19%2Fpakistan-is-an-authoritarian-regime-democracy-index-2023-only-asian-country-in-the-category%2F%5C%22%3Edowngraded%3C%2Fa%3E%20Pakistan%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98hybrid%20regime%E2%80%99%20to%20an%20%E2%80%98authoritarian%20regime.%E2%80%99%20Currently%2C%20Pakistan%20is%20categorised%20as%20an%20authoritarian%20regime%20where%20there%20is%20no%20free%20speech%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mir%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20still%20journalists%2C%20despite%20the%20risks%2C%20continue%20to%20speak%20the%20truth%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708958645000%2C%22vi