0unacceptable%20to%20the%20people%20who%20were%20once%20represented%20by%20four%20MLAs%2C%20MLCs%2C%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Legislative%20Council%20and%20an%20MP.%20Today%2C%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20political%20representation%20lies%20restricted%20to%20a%20single%20MP%20without%20portfolio%20and%20two%20Autonomous%20Hill%20Development%20Councils%20in%20each%20district%20which%20jostle%20even%20with%20the%20deputy%20commissioner%20over%20the%20ambiguous%20distribution%20of%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20demands%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Full%20statehood%20for%20Ladakh%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Inclusion%20in%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%3Cbr%3E%5Cn3.%20Establishment%20of%20a%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20in%20Ladakh%20(for%20secure%20jobs)%3Cbr%3E%5Cn4.%20Two%20MPs%20for%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20Ladakh%20has%20a%20population%20of%20roughly%20three%20lakh.%20The%20twin%20districts%20of%20Leh%20and%20Kargil%20were%20formerly%20administered%20just%20fine%20by%20only%20two%20deputy%20commissioners%20respectively.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20UT%20of%20Ladakh%20is%20governed%20by%20a%20Lt%20Governor%2C%20an%20advisor%2C%20a%20principal%20secretary%2C%20three%20commissioner%20secretaries%2C%20four%20secretaries%2C%20one%20IG%20Ladakh%20Police%2C%20DIGs%2C%20two%20SSPs%2C%20five%20SPs%20and%20an%20abundance%20of%20officers%20from%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20services%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20cobweb%20of%20bureaucracy.%20Shockingly%2C%20after%20more%20than%20four%20years%2C%20the%20Union%20Territory%20of%20Ladakh%20does%20not%20have%20gazetted%20recruitment%20rules%2C%20no%20domicile%20clarity%20and%20no%20idea%20of%20the%20indigenous%20tribes%20in%20Ladakh%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20has%20an%20industrial%20policy%20in%20place%20which%20raises%20concern%20for%20the%20fragile%20ecology%20of%20the%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20indigenous%20voices%20in%20key%20policy%20decisions%20is%20the%20primary%20trigger%20for%20the%20protests.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20a%20plethora%20of%20questionable%20administrative%20decisions%20%E2%80%93%20ranging%20from%20the%20strategic%20to%20the%20everyday%20%E2%80%93%20taken%20post%20the%20dilution%20of%20Article%20370.%20The%20chaotic%20evacuations%20during%20COVID%2C%20no%20recruitment%20to%20gazetted%20positions%20and%20only%20negligible%20recruitment%20to%20non-gazetted%20ones%2C%20and%20a%20steep%20rise%20in%20contractualisation%2C%20have%20intensified%20difficulties.%20Further%2C%20the%20people%20are%20facing%20the%20brunt%20of%20price%20rise%20in%20essential%20commodities%20like%20sugar%20and%20kerosene%20and%20have%20trouble%20procuring%20the%20same%20from%20ration%20shops.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20decisions%20by%20the%20government%20to%20earmark%20community%20lands%20as%20state%20land%2C%20reassign%20the%20power%20of%20land%20documentation%20to%20the%20collector%2C%20formulate%20an%20industrial%20policy%20inimical%20to%20local%20interests%2C%20undertake%20coercive%20GST%20collection%2C%20fiddle%20with%20the%20recruitment%20process%20in%20Ladakh%20University%2C%20and%20introduce%20a%20lapse-able%20budget%20have%20only%20increased%20the%20distance%20between%20the%20government%20and%20the%20governed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26165210%2FGFZGOAxbIAAWkgf.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26165210%2FGFZGOAxbIAAWkgf.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26165210%2FGFZGOAxbIAAWkgf-300x134.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26165210%2FGFZGOAxbIAAWkgf-1024x457.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698963%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22535%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20February%203%20protest%20in%20Leh.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40SajjadKargili_%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2013%2C%20the%20Ladakh%20Research%20Scholar%20Forum%20cautioned%20the%20administration%20on%20%E2%80%98The%20Constitution%20(Jammu%20and%20Kashmir)%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20Order%20(Amendment)%20Bill%E2%80%99%2C%202024.%20Out%20of%20sheer%20negligence%2C%20the%20government%20failed%20to%20de-notify%20the%20Gujjar%2C%20Bakarwal%2C%20Gaddi%20and%20Sippi%20tribes%20from%20Ladakh%20%E2%80%93%20though%20they%20do%20not%20exist%20in%20Ladakh.%20This%20threatens%20not%20just%20the%20identity%20of%20Ladakh%20but%20also%20reflects%20the%20callousness%20of%20those%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tribes%20in%20Ladakh%20suffer%2C%20feeling%20alienated%20and%20helpless%20in%20their%20own%20land%2C%20the%20extravagance%20of%20the%20new%20ruling%20coterie%20of%20bureaucrats%20%E2%80%93%20at%20government%20expense%20%E2%80%93%20have%20added%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire.%20The%20February%203%20mega%20protest%20held%20at%20Leh%20was%20the%20culmination%20of%20protest%20calls%20since%202020.%20This%20protest%20was%20a%20show%20of%20strength%20and%20a%20final%20declaration%20of%20the%20four-point%20agenda%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh.%20Threats%20to%20boycott%20the%20LAHDC%20Leh%20elections%202020%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Delhi%20Chalo%E2%80%99%20last%20winter%20were%20major%20protests%20where%20the%20ministry%20had%20to%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%202%20this%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmha-constitutes-high-powered-committee-to-ensure-protection-of-land-and-employment-for-ladakh%2Farticle66331577.ece%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20constituted%20a%20High-Powered%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20(HPC)%20chaired%20by%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20home%20Nityanand%20Rai%20for%20the%20Union%20Territory%20of%20Ladakh.%20The%20HPC%2C%20in%20what%20was%20dubbed%20as%20the%20first%20official%20meeting%2C%20met%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20Apex%20Body%20and%20KDA%20on%20January%204%2C%20in%20which%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20representatives%20requested%20that%20they%20be%20presented%20the%20demands%20in%20a%20written%20format.%20After%20this%2C%20the%20second%20official%20meeting%20took%20place%20on%20February%2019%20and%20the%20third%20took%20place%20last%20Saturday.%20The%20developments%20from%20those%20meetings%20are%3A%20formation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98Sub%20Committee%E2%80%99%20which%20reduced%20the%20delegation%20from%2014%20to%20six%20members%3B%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20two%20MPs%20being%20dropped%20citing%20constitutional%20constraints%20on%20delimitation.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20is%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20HPC%2C%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20even%20the%20MoS%20in%20the%20last%20meeting%20raised%20doubts%20on%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20resolving%20matters.%20Meanwhile%2C%20calls%20to%20resume%20a%20%E2%80%98fast%20unto%20death%E2%80%99%20by%20some%20leaders%20have%20started%20finding%20voice%20again%2C%20should%20the%20talks%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peaceful%20and%20Gandhian%20approach%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20to%20put%20forth%20their%20just%20demands%20after%20four%20years%20of%20governance%20failures%20must%20be%20met%20with%20reciprocal%20humility%20and%20seriousness%20from%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMutasif%20Hussain%20is%20the%20Chief%20Coordinator%2C%20Ladakh%20Research%20Scholars%20Forum.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708955118000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26165002%2FGFZGOAta4AAFotw.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-roots-of-discontent-in-ladakh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20mass%20mobilisation%20in%20Leh%20on%20February%203%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20are%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20current%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20and%20need%20their%20four-point%20agenda%20to%20be%20taken%20seriously.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-roots-of-discontent-in-ladakh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Born%20Out%20of%20a%20Mom%E2%80%99s%20Mission%20To%20Build%20a%20Toxin-Free%20Home%2C%20This%20Brand%20Earns%20Her%20Rs%203%20Crore%2FMonth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20turn%20back%20the%20clock%2C%20approximately%20three%20years.%20On%2022%20March%2C%202020%2C%20India%20entered%20its%20first%20pandemic-induced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261522%2Fquarantine-home-baker-noida-cakes-breads-shweta-joshi-youtube%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elockdown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20restricting%20us%20all%20to%20our%20homes.%20It%20was%20a%20period%20when%20families%20came%20together%20to%20cook%2C%20clean%2C%20and%20tackle%20household%20chores%20collectively.%20Even%20the%20children%2C%20with%20their%20newfound%20time%20at%20home%2C%20lent%20a%20helping%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20scene%20unfolded%20at%20Simran%20Khara%E2%80%99s%20house%20in%20Delhi.%20The%2042-year-old%2C%20along%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20then%20five-year-old%20daughter%2C%20spent%20much%20of%20their%20time%20on%20household%20chores.%20After%20a%20few%20days%2C%20Simran%20started%20studying%20the%20labels%20of%20the%20dishwashing%20and%20floor%20cleaning%20products%20she%20was%20using%20at%20home.%20She%20recognised%20the%20presence%20of%20harmful%20chemicals%20in%20these%20cleaners%2C%20which%20posed%20risks%20to%20her%20daughter%20and%20even%20the%20surfaces%20they%20cleaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20longer%20at%20ease%20with%20her%20daughter%20participating%20in%20cleaning%20activities%20due%20to%20the%20potential%20exposure%20to%20these%20toxic%20chemicals%2C%20Simran%2C%20a%20concerned%20mother%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20MBA%20graduate%20with%2014%20years%20of%20corporate%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20resolved%20to%20develop%20a%20line%20of%20eco-friendly%20home%20cleaners%20that%20would%20prioritise%20child%20and%20pet%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20months%20of%20research%2C%20Simran%20Khara%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20Juggernaut%20Books%2C%20launched%20Koparo%20Clean%20in%20February%202021.%20Koparo%20Clean%20is%20a%20home-care%20product%20brandboasting%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%E2%80%9D%20formulations%20crafted%20from%20plant-based%20ingredients%20such%20as%20coconuts%20(%3Cem%3Ekopra%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20entrepreneurial%20journey%20gained%20national%20attention%20when%20she%20appeared%20on%20Shark%20Tank%20Season%203%2C%20where%20she%20secured%20a%20substantial%20investment%20of%20Rs%2070%20lakh%20from%20%E2%80%98Sharks%E2%80%99%20Vineeta%20Singh%20and%20Aman%20Gupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIn%20search%20of%20a%20toxin-free%20cleaning%20product%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201067px)%20100vw%2C%201067px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fkoparo-1708954181.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Simran%20started%20Koparo%20as%20she%20wanted%20her%20daughter%20to%20be%20exposed%20to%20toxin-free%20cleaners%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fkoparo-1708954181.jpeg%201067w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fkoparo-1708954181-200x300.jpeg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fkoparo-1708954181-500x750.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.th